== C. Viper Patch ==
* C. Viper released
<br>

== '''Universal Changes''' ==
* '''Whiffed {{clr|L|Lights}} > {{clr|DR|Drive Rush}}:''' fixed an issue where some normals would not cancel near the end of the whiff animation but would cancel on hit/block, allowing players to option select the {{clr|DR|DR}} cancel. Applies to:
** A.K.I. {{clr|L|5LK}}
** Chun-Li {{clr|L|2LK}}
** Ed {{clr|L|2LK}}
** Elena {{clr|L|5LK}}
** Mai {{clr|L|5LK}}
** Sagat {{clr|L|5LK}}
<br>

* '''{{clr|DR|Drive Rush Cancel}} overlap with Special Move commands:''' fixed an issue where some normals would cancel into a special move when input with the Parry buttons, rather than canceling into {{clr|DR|Drive Rush}}. Applies to:
** A.K.I. {{clr|L|5LK}}
** Akuma {{clr|L|2LP}}
** Elena {{clr|L|5LP}}
** M. Bison {{clr|L|5LP}}
** Marisa {{clr|L|2LP}}
** Sagat {{clr|L|2LP}}, {{clr|M|2MP}}~{{clr|H|HP}}
<br>

* '''{{clr|SA|Super Art}} affecting opponent's Drive Gauge recovery:''' fixed an issue where certain {{clr|SA|Supers}} with a lock-in animation would stop a burned out opponent's passive Drive Gauge regeneration during the animation. Applies to:
** Akuma {{clr|SA|SA2}}
** Cammy {{clr|SA|SA2}} (ground/air)
** E. Honda {{clr|SA|SA2}}
** Elena {{clr|SA|SA2}}
** Kimberly {{clr|SA|SA2}} (ground/air)
** M. Bison {{clr|SA|SA2}}
** Marisa {{clr|SA|Held SA1}}, {{clr|SA|SA2}} (cinematic hit)
** Sagat {{clr|SA|SA2}} (all variations)
<br>

* '''{{clr|SA|Super Art}} gauge scaling:''' fixed an issue where some {{clr|SA|Supers}} that incur scaling penalties to their meter gain (Chun-Li/Dee Jay {{clr|SA|SA2}}) would have follow-up hits scaled even further if landed in a combo with 16 or more hits
<br>

== '''Character Changes''' ==

=== '''Cammy''' ===
* {{clr|L|LK Spiral Arrow}} ({{clr|L|236LK}}) active frame 6~ increased juggle time vs. airborne opponents
** Ensures that {{clr|H|5HP}}~{{clr|H|HK}} > {{clr|L|236LK}} can always juggle into 623K near the corner
<br>

=== '''Chun-Li''' ===
* {{clr|OD|OD Tensho Kicks}} ({{clr|OD|22KK}}) expanded collision box upward and expanded final hitbox forward
** Fixes an issue where the 2nd attack could go in the wrong direction at some distances
<br>

=== '''Dee Jay''' ===
* {{clr|OD|OD Waning Moon}} ({{clr|OD|214KK}}~{{clr|M|MK}}) expanded the collision box upward on frames 16-19
** Primarily intended to fix issue with Modern controls Assist Combo 3 whiffing under opponents
<br>

=== '''Elena''' ===
* Moon Glider (214P/{{clr|OD|PP}}~6P) hitstop on block increased 11 → 13 to match the on-hit version
** This prevents an option select where follow-ups could be performed only on hit, bypassing the need to hitconfirm it
<br>

=== '''Guile''' ===
* {{clr|L|2LK}} fixed issue where Guile had a {{clr|PC|Punish Counter}} hurtbox 1f after the end of recovery
** Fixed issue where a chained {{clr|L|5LP}}/{{clr|L|2LP}}/{{clr|L|2LK}} would come out when trying to buffer a technique that uses {{clr|L|LP}} or {{clr|L|LK}} buttons
<br>

=== '''Jamie''' ===
* Freeflow Strikes Drink Lv.4 (236P) expanded collision box upward when first attack hits to prevent later hits from whiffing under the opponent
<br>

=== '''JP''' ===
* {{clr|OD|OD Torbalan}} ({{clr|OD|236KK}}) added a combo-only hitbox to prevent whiffing on midair opponents
<br>

=== '''M. Bison''' ===
* Throw Escape now functions properly when inputs overlap with [[Street_Fighter_6/M.Bison#Hidden_Arts|special moves]] exclusive to SiRN Bison
* Head Press ([2]8K~K) no longer bounces back when triggering counter moves (JP's Amnesia, Marisa's {{clr|SA|Held SA1}}) making it no longer able to avoid punishment
<br>

=== '''Manon''' ===
* Modern Control inputs for Renversé (236P) follow-ups (Feint and Grand Fouetté kick) changed to fix input overlap issues when canceling into {{clr|SA|SA3}}
** Renversé Feint changed from {{clr|DR|2[S]}} to {{clr|DR|2S}}~{{clr|L|[L]}} 
** Grand Fouetté changed from {{clr|DR|2S}}~X to {{clr|DR|2S}}~{{clr|M|M}} 
<br>

=== '''Mai''' ===
* {{clr|M|MP Ryuuenbu}} ({{clr|M|214MP}}) no longer applies 20% starter scaling and 2-hit combo scaling when only the 2nd hit connects
* {{clr|3|Flame}} {{clr|M|MP Ryuuenbu}} ({{clr|3|F}}.{{clr|M|214MP}}) no longer applies 20% starter scaling when only the 2nd hit connects
<br>

=== '''Ryu''' ===
* {{clr|OD|OD Denjin Hashogeki}} ({{clr|OD|214PP}}) chip damage corrected from 400 → 200
<br>

=== '''Terry''' ===
* {{clr|OD|OD Quick Burn}} ({{clr|OD|214}}{{clr|L|LP}}{{clr|M|MP}}) cancel window into {{clr|SA|SA2/SA3}} now comes out on the 2nd active frame of the 2nd hit
** Prevents a combo drop that would occur when the 2nd hit's first active frame whiffed
<br>

=== '''Zangief''' ===
* Double Lariat (Modern Controls: {{clr|M|M}}+{{clr|H|H}}) now comes out properly instead of a Throw when inputting {{clr|L|L}}+{{clr|M|M}}+{{clr|H|H}} during Burnout
<br>